definitions.definition: ( uncountable , physical chemistry ) Matter in an intermediate state between liquid and plasma that can be contained only if it is fully surrounded by a solid (or in a bubble of liquid , or held together by gravitational pull); it can condense into a liquid, or can (rarely) become a solid directly by deposition .
examples: A lot of gas had escaped from the cylinder.

subdefinitions.definition: ( uncountable ) A flammable gaseous hydrocarbon or hydrocarbon mixture used as a fuel, e.g. for cooking, heating, electricity generation or as a fuel in internal combustion engines in vehicles, especially natural gas .
examples: Gas -fired power stations have largely replaced coal-burning ones.
The artillery fired gas shells into the enemy trenches.

definitions.definition: ( countable , physical chemistry ) A chemical element or compound in such a state.
examples: The atmosphere is made up of a number of different gases .

definitions.definition: ( countable ) A hob on a gas cooker .
examples: She turned the gas on, put the potatoes on, then lit the oven.

definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) Methane or other waste gases trapped in one's belly as a result of the digestive process; flatus .
examples: My tummy hurts so bad – I have gas .

definitions.definition: ( business , often attributive ) The supply of natural gas , as a utility .
( slang , dated ) A humorous or entertaining event , person , or thing .
( slang ) Frothy or boastful talk ; chatter .

examples: The closer threw him nothing but gas .

definitions.definition: ( medicine , colloquial ) Arterial or venous blood gas.
